results.name: Number of n-digit Fibonacci numbers.
comment: a(1)=7 because the Fibonacci numbers having one digit are the first seven; then the next five have two digits, so a(2)=5.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
Ron Knott, [Number of digits in Fib(i)] : Calculator.
xref: Essentially the same as A050815, which is the main entry for this sequence. Cf. A000045, A060384.
